# Force LF line endings for shell scripts and dotfiles.
# Without this, files edited on Windows or with certain editors get
# CRLF endings and break when piped to bash on Linux:
#   bash: línea 14: $'\r': orden no encontrada
# See: https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/getting-started-with-git/configuring-git-to-handle-line-endings
*.sh        text eol=lf
*.zshrc     text eol=lf
*.bashrc    text eol=lf
*.bash      text eol=lf
README.md   text eol=lf
*.lua       text eol=lf
*.vim       text eol=lf